# main.py Rules

## What Lives Here (all of it)

- FastAPI app instance
- Auth middleware (calls `auth.resolve_request`, enforces tier write-drop)
- Catch-all mock router (dispatches to `BaseMock` subclasses)
- `/registry` endpoint
- `/auth/magic` and `/auth/verify` endpoints
- `/usage` endpoint
- APScheduler cron setup (calls `recorder.run_all()`)
- Static file mount for `dashboard/`

## Do NOT Split

- No new router files. The catch-all route is ~15 LOC.
- No `onboarding.py`. Magic link endpoints are two functions.
- No `usage.py`. Usage is one GET handler reading from `store`.

## LOC Budget: ~100 lines

If `main.py` exceeds 120 lines, something that belongs in `auth.py`, `store.py`, or `models.py` has leaked in. Move it there.

## Autodiscovery Only

Mock routing MUST use `BaseMock.__subclasses__()` to find integrations. Never a hardcoded import list. Adding `mocks/foo.py` must be sufficient to register it.
